The game Samoan Game is played by two players on a 12x6 rectangle board with square tiling. All players play with Markers. Rules for Pieces: Markers step adjacent or hop adjacent. Players take turns moving. Setup: Place a Marker for player one at the left sites of the board expanded by 1 steps. Place a Marker for player two at the right sites of the board expanded by 1 steps.. Rules: Move one of your pieces. Aim: If the next player cannot move, the next player loses. The Samoan Game (Ludii 1) ruleset.
